---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-20'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie policy — oriz · cards"
  description="What cookies cards.oriz.in uses."
>
  <div class="spine-prose">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow mono">
        <a href="/">cards</a> / <a href="/legal/">legal</a> / cookies
      </p>
      <h1>cookie policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p>
        cards.oriz.in uses the smallest set of cookies and storage we can get
        away with.
      </p>

      <h2>What we set</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Compare drawer</strong> — <code>sessionStorage</code> key
          <code>oriz:cards:compare</code> stores the cards you have selected
          for comparison so they survive a page navigation. Cleared when you
          close the tab.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Auth session</strong> — when you sign in, Firebase
          Authentication sets cookies on <code>auth.oriz.in</code> so you stay
          logged in across every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site. These are
          first-party and essential.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third parties</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set anti-abuse cookies (Turnstile,
          bot management). These are essential for site availability.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Opting out</h2>
      <p>
        You can clear localStorage, sessionStorage, and cookies for any oriz
        domain from your browser's site-data settings. Auth will reset.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
